<TITLE> One dies in lightning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, May 3 (bdnews24.com)  A man was killed and four others were injured in lightning in Chapainawabganj on Monday. The deceased Arshad Ali, 25, is the son of Abdul Kaium from Bakher Ali village under Char Bagdanga Union of the Sadr upazila. The injured are Arshad's brother Abdul Bari, 30, wife Merina Khatun, 26, sister Rehana Khatun, 25, and his cousin Nazma Khatun, 20. Akramul Haque, member of ward 1 of Char Bagdanga Union Parishad, said that Akram had died on the spot and four others had been injured in the lightning at around 4pm when they were working at home. The injured were given treatment locally. bdn
